nlm.nih.gov/25668012/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=A+multi-centre+randomised+trial+comparing+ultrasound+vs+mammography+for+screening+breast+cancer+in+high-risk+Chinese+women&amp;author=S+Shen&amp;author=Y+Zhou&amp;author=Y+Xu&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;journal=Br+J+Cancer&amp;pages=998-1004&amp;doi=10.1038%2Fbjc.2015.33&amp;pmid=25668012">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">10.</div><div id="r10" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Ohuchi N, Suzuki A, Sobue T, et al. Sensitivity and specificity of mammography and adjunctive ultrasonography to screen for breast cancer in the Japan Strategic Anti-cancer Randomized Trial (J-START): a randomised controlled trial. <em>Lancet</em> 2016;387(10016):341–348.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(15)00774-6">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26547101/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Sensitivity+and+specificity+of+mammography+and+adjunctive+ultrasonography+to+screen+for+breast+cancer+in+the+Japan+Strategic+Anti-cancer+Randomized+Trial+%28J-START%29%3A+a+randomised+controlled+trial&amp;author=N+Ohuchi&amp;author=A+Suzuki&amp;author=T+Sobue&amp;publication_year=2016&amp;journal=Lancet&amp;pages=341-348&amp;doi=10.1016%2FS0140-6736%2815%2900774-6&amp;pmid=26547101">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">11.</div><div id="r11" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Berg WA, Bandos AI, Mendelson EB, Lehrer D, Jong RA, Pisano ED. Ultrasound as the primary screening test for breast cancer: analysis from ACRIN 6666. <em>J Natl Cancer Inst</em> 2015